DNS Leak Server — Architecture
================================

A self-contained DNS leak testing service. Clients resolve
HMAC-signed subdomains; the server captures which DNS resolver
made the query and returns it via HTTPS in the same request.


Query Flow
----------

    Client (browser)
      │
      │  fetch("https://{random}-{hmac}-{ts}.dns-leak-server.phantom.tc/")
      │
      ▼
    Browser DNS Resolver
      │
      │  UDP :53 — "What is {random}-{hmac}-{ts}.dns-leak-server.phantom.tc?"
      │
      ▼
    DNS Leak Server (Go, UDP :53)
      │  1. Parse: random, hmac, timestamp
      │  2. Verify timestamp (TTL window, default 30s)
      │  3. Verify HMAC(random + timestamp, shared_secret)
      │  4. Capture resolver IP (who asked)
      │  5. Store in memory: cache[random] = resolver_ip
      │  6. Respond with A record → server's own IP
      │
      ▼
    Browser connects to server IP
      │
      │  HTTPS :443 — GET /
      │  Host: {random}-{hmac}-{ts}.dns-leak-server.phantom.tc
      │
      ▼
    DNS Leak Server (Go, HTTPS :443)
      │  1. Parse random from Host header
      │  2. LoadAndDelete(random) from cache
      │  3. Return JSON: {"resolver_ip": "8.8.8.8"}
      │
      ▼
    Client receives resolver IP directly


Subdomain Format
----------------

    {random}-{hmac}-{timestamp}.dns-leak-server.phantom.tc

    random    16 hex chars, unique per query
    hmac      HMAC-SHA256(random + timestamp, shared_secret)[:16]
    timestamp Unix seconds (stateless expiry)

    Single subdomain level — wildcard TLS cert matches.
    Dash-separated — parsed by splitting on "-".


Token Security
--------------

    Worker generates:  random + timestamp → HMAC → subdomain
    DNS server verifies: HMAC + timestamp window
    No valid subdomain can be forged without shared_secret.
    Expired tokens rejected without state lookup.


Container Architecture
----------------------

    docker-compose.yml
    ├── dns-leak-server (Go binary)
    │     network_mode: host
    │     UDP :53  — DNS handler (HMAC verify + resolver capture)
    │     TCP :443 — HTTPS handler (resolver IP response)
    │     env_file: .env
    │     secrets: shared_secret, tls_cert, tls_key
    │
    └── Secrets (Docker secrets from files)
          /run/secrets/shared_secret
          /run/secrets/tls_cert
          /run/secrets/tls_key


Zone Infrastructure
-------------------

    DNS server also handles zone queries for delegation:

    SOA   dns-leak-server.phantom.tc  → ns-leak-1.phantom.tc
    NS    dns-leak-server.phantom.tc  → ns-leak-1.phantom.tc
    CAA   dns-leak-server.phantom.tc  → issue "letsencrypt.org"

    Non-matching queries receive REFUSED.


ACME Certificate Issuance
-------------------------

    acme/ directory contains a minimal Go DNS server + certbot
    for wildcard certificate issuance via DNS-01 challenge.

    tools/prod.sh setup:
      1. Generates shared_secret (openssl rand -hex 32)
      2. Stops main DNS server (frees port 53)
      3. Runs ACME container:
         - Go DNS server handles _acme-challenge TXT + CAA + SOA
         - Certbot requests *.dns-leak-server.phantom.tc
         - Certificate saved to secrets/certs/
      4. Outputs tls_cert + tls_key

    tools/prod.sh renew-cert:
      Same flow, for renewal (cron: every 60 days).


